overview: The user aimed to transform their sleep questionnaire app from a
  generic, functional design into a visually appealing and professional
  experience. The assistant initiated a comprehensive aesthetic overhaul,
  starting with a new sleep-themed color palette and custom utility classes.
  This involved redesigning the main form layout with subtle background effects
  and an enhanced progress indicator, and polishing core UI components like
  checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders for better visual feedback. All
  questionnaire sections received consistent styling, replacing bland gray boxes
  with themed card-like groupings. A critical React console error related to
  null input values was also identified and fixed. Following user feedback, the
  assistant further refined alert colors, increased border opacities for better
  definition, and standardized the card header gradients in the report section,
  eliminating previous jarring color inconsistencies. The iterative process,
  despite browser tool limitations, successfully delivered a cohesive, calming,
  and professional aesthetic for the application.
